     />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After long consideration of what engine to use, I decided to start using Unity.\nI’m still not 100% sure, will reconsider it after some time.\nBut for now it looks like the best available option for my needs.</p>\n<p>I started with a very technical approach.\nCurrently, game doesn’t have a name or story - only mechanics that I still need to develop.\nWhy is that? you ask. Well, good question. I wanted to separate concerns.\nInventing the story and writing the code, when both of these things are new to me is overwhelming.\nI decided to concentrate on one thing and then improve the other.</p>\n<p>If you’re interested to follow the process, you should follow me on twitter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/artemdemo\">@artemdemo</a>.\nI regularly post new things there.\nI’ll also update the blog, but obviously it will take more time to do.</p>\n<video autoplay loop style=\"width: 100%\">\n  <source src=\"/29dc6b01fba52bf8092d171b5e33724d/first-game-video.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" />\n</video>","frontmatter":{"title":"I started new game experiment","date":"January 09, 2021","tags":["game","pixel art","unity"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/20210103-game-experiment/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/20210101-learning-pixel-art/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"I started to learn pixel art","tags":["studying","pixel art"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/20210118-unity-object-moves-too-fast-for-the-collider-to-catch/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Object moves too fast for the collider to catch (solution for unity)","tags":["game","unity"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}